title: Lottery player wins $2.6M in Sheboygan
text:
Lottery player wins $2.6M in Sheboygan Kali Thiel , Sheboygan Press Media 12 p.m. CDT October 19, 2015 A winning Lottery ticket, worth $1.5 million after taxes, has been sold in Sheboygan. (Photo: Associated Press) 456 CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
A Sheboygan gas station and convenience store has sold a winning multi-million dollar Wisconsin Lottery ticket. 
The Wisconsin Lottery has posted on its website that an unidentified player matched all six numbers in Saturday night's MegaBucks jackpot to win $2.6 million. 
The ticket was sold at Citgo 14, 610 S. 14th St. 
This isn't the first time in recent years that Sheboygan County has had a big winner. 
Last year in June, two different Sheboygan men each collected $673,500, the after-tax payment for their $1 million Powerball winning tickets. Both tickets were sold at QMart locations in Sheboygan County. 
In addition, a $199,000 winning Badger 5 ticket was sold at Piggly Wiggly in Sheboygan for a May 2014 drawing.
